BSE - FRANCE
************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
[see: BSE - France 20000103221951]
[1]
Date: Fri, 07 Jan 2000 09:49:34 -0800
From: *Ivan Sache* <sache@platon.grignon.inra.fr>
Source: French radio

A cow showing symptoms of BSE was found on a farm in the department of
Creuse, region Limousin (France). The whole herd will be slaughtered in the
forthcoming days Slaughtering of the whole herd in which a single case of
BSE has been detected is a standard sanitation measure in France.
This is the first time BSE is reported in the Limousine race. Limousine meat
is highly appreciated by consumers due to its top organo-leptic quality.
Until now, meat was expected not to be contaminated by BSE because several
farms in the producing area use traditional breeding methods.
